==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Synchysis
<hw>Syn"chy*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/, fr. <?/ to confound; <grk>sy`n</grk> with + <?/ to pour.]</ety>
<def>A derangement or confusion of any kind, as of words in a sentence,
or of humors in the eye.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sparkling synchysis</b></col> <fld>(Med.)</fld>, <cd>a
condition in which the vitreous humor is softened and contains sparkling
scales of cholesterin.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Synclastic</ent>⟦br⟧
